==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hollo
<hw>Hol*lo"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>interj. & n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Halloo</er>, and cf. <er>Holla</er>.]</ety> <def>Ho there; stop;
attend; hence, a loud cry or a call to attract attention; a
halloo.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And every day, for food or play,⟦br⟧
Came to the mariner's <qex>hollo</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hollo</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hollo
<hw>Hol"lo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Holloed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Holloing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See <er>Hollo</er>,
<ets>interj</ets>., and cf. <er>Halloo</er>.]</ety> <def>To call out or
exclaim; to halloo.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Holloa</ent>⟦br⟧
